# No inline imports

Prefer static imports at the top of the module. Avoid inline static imports in function bodies, type annotations, or interface fields unless there is a strict circular-dependency reason and it is documented.

Dynamic `import()` is allowed when it is the correct runtime mechanism for lazy loading, code splitting, optional dependencies, environment-gated modules, or plugin loading. Document the reason when it is not obvious from local context.
